## Adding a New Entity

Follow these steps **in order**. Do not skip steps.

### Step 1: Generate the entity

```bash
php bin/console make:entity
```

This creates `src/Entity/MyEntity.php` and `src/Repository/MyEntityRepository.php`.

### Step 2: Define fields using PHP attributes

```php
<?php

declare(strict_types=1);

namespace App\Entity;

use App\Repository\MyEntityRepository;
use Doctrine\ORM\Mapping as ORM;
use Symfony\Component\Uid\Uuid;

#[ORM\Entity(repositoryClass: MyEntityRepository::class)]
#[ORM\Table(name: 'my_entities')]
#[ORM\HasLifecycleCallbacks]
class MyEntity
{
    #[ORM\Id]
    #[ORM\Column(type: 'uuid', unique: true)]
    private Uuid $id;

    #[ORM\Column(length: 255)]
    private string $name;

    #[ORM\Column]
    private \DateTimeImmutable $createdAt;

    #[ORM\Column]
    private \DateTimeImmutable $updatedAt;

    public function __construct(string $name)
    {
        $this->id = Uuid::v7();
        $this->name = $name;
        $this->createdAt = new \DateTimeImmutable();
        $this->updatedAt = new \DateTimeImmutable();
    }

    #[ORM\PreUpdate]
    public function onPreUpdate(): void
    {
        $this->updatedAt = new \DateTimeImmutable();
    }

    public function getId(): Uuid { return $this->id; }
    public function getName(): string { return $this->name; }
    public function setName(string $name): void { $this->name = $name; }
}
```

### Step 3: Generate and review the migration

```bash
php bin/console make:migration
# Review the generated file in migrations/
php bin/console doctrine:migrations:migrate --no-interaction
```

**Never skip the review.** Check for unexpected `DROP` statements.

### Step 4: Write a repository method (never use generic `findBy` in services)

```php
// src/Repository/MyEntityRepository.php
public function findByName(string $name): ?MyEntity
{
    return $this->createQueryBuilder('e')
        ->andWhere('e.name = :name')
        ->setParameter('name', $name)
        ->getQuery()
        ->getOneOrNullResult();
}
```

### Step 5: Create or extend a service

```php
// src/Service/MyEntityService.php
final class MyEntityService
{
    public function __construct(
        private readonly MyEntityRepository $repository,
        private readonly EntityManagerInterface $em,
    ) {}

    public function create(string $name): MyEntity
    {
        $entity = new MyEntity($name);
        $this->em->persist($entity);
        $this->em->flush();
        return $entity;
    }
}
```

