## Common Pitfalls

| Pitfall | Correct Approach |
|---------|-----------------|
| `$em->flush()` in controller | Move flush to the service method |
| `findBy(['email' => $email])` in a service | Add `findByEmail(string $email)` to the repository |
| `new DateTime()` on an entity | Use `new \DateTimeImmutable()` |
| `$container->get(UserService::class)` | Inject `UserService` via constructor |
| Editing a committed migration | Generate a new migration with `make:migration` |
| Catching `\Exception` broadly | Catch specific exceptions; let unknown ones bubble up |
| `ROLE_ADMIN` check in controller | Create a `UserVoter` with a semantic attribute |
| Serializing a whole entity | Use serialization groups; never expose internal fields |
| Skipping tests for "trivial" code | Write at least one test per public method |

