## When to Write an ADR

Write a new ADR in `docs/adrs/` when:

- Adding a new Composer dependency (especially a framework-level one)
- Introducing a new architectural pattern not described in `docs/architecture.md`
- Making a decision between two valid approaches
- Changing the authentication or authorization strategy
- Planning a breaking API change

Use the format in `docs/ways-of-working.md`. File as `docs/adrs/NNNN-kebab-title.md`.
